### Compute the ROE using the derived formula.

ROE is calculated by dividing the sustainable growth rate by the retention ratio.
$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Return on Equity}&= \dfrac{12\%}{75\%}\\[15pt]

&= 0.16 \times 100\\[15pt]

&= \boxed{\textbf{16\%}}


\end{aligned}
$$


Therefore, the return on equity is **16%**.

### Compute the sales.

The assets to sales ratio are 0.85. 

The formula for computing the sales is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Sales}&= \dfrac{\text{Total Assets}}{\text{Assets to Sales Ratio}}\\[15pt]

&= \boxed{\dfrac{\text{Total Assets}}{0.85}}
\end{aligned}
$$


Therefore, the total sales are **total assets/0.85**.

### Compute the total assets.


The assets are calculated by multiplying equity with a 1+debt equity ratio.

The formula is as follows.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Assets}&= \text{Equity} \times \text{(1 + Debt Equity Ratio)}\\[15pt]

&= \boxed{\text{Equity(1.90)}}

\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the total assets are **equity(1.90)**.
